(en) Gusum’s use from above 1933. There have been iron and brass mills in the locality since the 1600s. At the time of the picture and for another time the mill was the completely dominant industry in the resort and offered a large part of the community’s inhabitants jobs. For the general public, zippers are possibly the most famous product in use.
The photograph is a contact-copied work material that does not make the airline’s finished postcard fair - https://www.europeana.eu/item/73/S_OM_photo_OMFA000080. AB Flygtrafik. Östergötlands museum - http://digitaltmuseum.se/021016419434. Public Domain Mark - http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/mark/1.0/
